# {VAULT_NAME} — second-brain vault

> This block is the second-brain vault context. It can stand alone in this directory, or be merged into a parent CLAUDE.md by copy-pasting the section below.

## On every session start

1. Read `vault.md` for the atom contract, walking conventions, and verb specs.
2. Read `goals.md` for active threads.
3. Glance at `inbox/` (count) and `notes/claims/` (last ~10 by mtime).
4. Surface a one-line orientation: "active threads: X, Y. Inbox: N. Recent: Z."

If `goals.md` looks stale (no progress >7 days), say so.

## What this directory is

A graph of atomic claims. Verbs: `/extract`, `/connect`, `/walk`, `/audit`, `/learn`, `/anneal`, `/init`, `/dream`. Surrender system (opt-in via `surrender.enabled` in `vault.yaml`): `/no-surrender` (v1), `/teach` (v2). Full contract and conventions in `vault.md`.
